    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::plugin_error_swallowing": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::plugin_error_swallowing",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Plugins systematically swallow errors \u2014 catch-log-return without propagation",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "src/plugins/signals-plugin.ts",
          "src/plugins/tips-plugin.ts",
          "src/plugins/sc-prices-plugin.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "18 try_catch blocks across plugins/ \u2014 all follow the pattern: catch error, log via observe() or ctx.logger, return early. No plugin propagates errors to the session loop. While individually reasonable (plugins shouldn't crash the loop), this means the loop has no visibility into whether plugins are silently failing. signals-plugin.ts catches and observes; tips-plugin.ts catches but only logs."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add a hookErrors array to the hook context (already present in BeforeSenseContext as hookErrors?) and populate it consistently in all plugin catch blocks. The session runner can then report aggregated plugin health after each phase.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "a575bb06"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
